{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":6000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":10000,"text":"And I feel like this whole evening has been very amazing to me."},{"time":14000,"text":"I feel it's sort of like the Vimalakirti Sutra,"},{"time":18000,"text":"an ancient work from ancient India"},{"time":21000,"text":"in which the Buddha appears at the beginning and a whole bunch of people"},{"time":27000,"text":"come to see him from the biggest city in the area, Vaishali,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and they bring some sort of jeweled parasols to make an offering to him."},{"time":35000,"text":"All the young people, actually, from the city."},{"time":38000,"text":"The old fogeys don't come because they're mad at Buddha,"},{"time":43000,"text":"because when he came to their city he accepted --"},{"time":45000,"text":"he always accepts the first invitation that comes to him, from whoever it is,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and the local geisha, a movie-star sort of person,"},{"time":53000,"text":"raced the elders of the city in a chariot and invited him first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"So he was hanging out with the movie star, and of course they were grumbling:"},{"time":60000,"text":"\"He's supposed to be religious and all this."},{"time":62000,"text":"What's he doing over there at Amrapali's house with all his 500 monks,\""},{"time":67000,"text":"and so on. They were all grumbling, and so they boycotted him."},{"time":71000,"text":"They wouldn't go listen to him."},{"time":72000,"text":"But the young people all came."},{"time":74000,"text":"And they brought this kind of a jeweled parasol, and they put it on the ground."},{"time":78000,"text":"And as soon as they had laid all these,"},{"time":80000,"text":"all their big stack of these jeweled parasols that they used to carry in ancient India,"},{"time":85000,"text":"he performed a kind of special effect which made it into a giant planetarium,"},{"time":92000,"text":"the wonder of the universe. Everyone looked in that, and they saw in there"},{"time":95000,"text":"the total interconnectedness of all life in all universes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"And of course, in the Buddhist cosmos there are millions and billions of planets"},{"time":103000,"text":"with human life on it,"},{"time":105000,"text":"and enlightened beings can see the life on all the other planets."},{"time":108000,"text":"So they don't -- when they look out and they see those lights that you showed"},{"time":111000,"text":"in the sky -- they don't just see sort of pieces of matter burning"},{"time":115000,"text":"or rocks or flames or gases exploding."},{"time":119000,"text":"They actually see landscapes and human beings"},{"time":121000,"text":"and gods and dragons and serpent beings and goddesses and things like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127000,"text":"He made that special effect at the beginning"},{"time":129000,"text":"to get everyone to think about interconnection"},{"time":132000,"text":"and interconnectedness and how everything in life was totally interconnected."},{"time":137000,"text":"And then Leilei -- I know his other name -- told us about interconnection,"},{"time":145000,"text":"and how we're all totally interconnected here,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and how we've all known each other. And of course in the Buddhist universe,"},{"time":151000,"text":"we've already done this already billions of times in many, many lifetimes in the past."},{"time":156000,"text":"And I didn't give the talk always. You did, and we had to watch you, and so forth."},{"time":165000,"text":"And we're all still trying to, I guess we're all trying to become TEDsters,"},{"time":169000,"text":"if that's a modern form of enlightenment."},{"time":173000,"text":"I guess so. Because in a way, if a TEDster relates to all the interconnectedness"},{"time":177000,"text":"of all the computers and everything, it's the forging of a mass awareness,"},{"time":183000,"text":"of where everybody can really know everything"},{"time":185000,"text":"that's going on everywhere in the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"And therefore it will become intolerable --"},{"time":189000,"text":"what compassion is, is where it will become intolerable for us,"},{"time":193000,"text":"totally intolerable that we sit here in comfort and in pleasure and enjoying"},{"time":199000,"text":"the life of the mind or whatever it is,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and there are people who are absolutely riddled with disease"},{"time":206000,"text":"and they cannot have a bite of food and they have no place,"},{"time":209000,"text":"or they're being brutalized by some terrible person and so forth."},{"time":212000,"text":"It just becomes intolerable."},{"time":214000,"text":"With all of us knowing everything, we're kind of forced by technology"},{"time":220000,"text":"to become Buddhas or something, to become enlightened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"And of course, we all will be deeply disappointed when we do."},{"time":230000,"text":"Because we think that because we are kind of tired of what we do,"},{"time":237000,"text":"a little bit tired, we do suffer."},{"time":239000,"text":"We do enjoy our misery in a certain way."},{"time":242000,"text":"We distract ourselves from our misery by running around somewhere,"},{"time":245000,"text":"but basically we all have this common misery"},{"time":247000,"text":"that we are sort of stuck inside our skins"},{"time":250000,"text":"and everyone else is out there."},{"time":253000,"text":"And occasionally we get together with another person stuck in their skin"},{"time":256000,"text":"and the two of us enjoy each other, and each one tries to get out of their own,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and ultimately it fails of course, and then we're back into this thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"Because our egocentric perception -- from the Buddha's point of view, misperception --"},{"time":271000,"text":"is that all we are is what is inside our skin."},{"time":275000,"text":"And it's inside and outside, self and other,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and other is all very different."},{"time":279000,"text":"And everyone here is unfortunately carrying that habitual perception,"},{"time":282000,"text":"a little bit, right?"},{"time":285000,"text":"You know, someone sitting next to you in a seat -- that's OK because you're in a theater,"},{"time":288000,"text":"but if you were sitting on a park bench and someone came up and sat that close to you,"},{"time":291000,"text":"you'd freak out."},{"time":293000,"text":"What do they want from me? Like, who's that?"},{"time":296000,"text":"And so you wouldn't sit that close to another person"},{"time":299000,"text":"because of your notion that it's you versus the universe -- that's all Buddha discovered."},{"time":305000,"text":"Because that cosmic basic idea that it is us all alone, each of us,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and everyone else is different,"},{"time":313000,"text":"then that puts us in an impossible situation, doesn't it?"},{"time":316000,"text":"Who is it who's going to get enough attention from the world?\n"},{"time":319000,"text":"Who's going to get enough out of the world?"},{"time":322000,"text":"Who's not going to be overrun by an infinite number of other beings --"},{"time":325000,"text":"if you're different from all the other beings?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"So where compassion comes is where you"},{"time":332000,"text":"surprisingly discover you lose yourself in some way:"},{"time":337000,"text":"through art, through meditation, through understanding, through knowledge actually,"},{"time":342000,"text":"knowing that you have no such boundary,"},{"time":344000,"text":"knowing your interconnectedness with other beings."},{"time":347000,"text":"You can experience yourself as the other beings"},{"time":350000,"text":"when you see through the delusion of being separated from them."},{"time":355000,"text":"When you do that, you're forced to feel what they feel."},{"time":358000,"text":"Luckily, they say -- I still am not sure --"},{"time":362000,"text":"but luckily, they say that when you reach that point because some people have said"},{"time":366000,"text":"in the Buddhist literature, they say, \"Oh who would really want to be compassionate?"},{"time":369000,"text":"How awful! I'm so miserable on my own. My head is aching."},{"time":374000,"text":"My bones are aching. I go from birth to death. I'm never satisfied."},{"time":377000,"text":"I never have enough, even if I'm a billionaire, I don't have enough."},{"time":380000,"text":"I need a hundred billion.\" So I'm like that."},{"time":383000,"text":"Imagine if I had to feel even a hundred other people's suffering."},{"time":389000,"text":"It would be terrible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"But apparently, this is a strange paradox of life."},{"time":394000,"text":"When you're no longer locked in yourself,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and as the wisdom or the intelligence or the scientific knowledge"},{"time":401000,"text":"of the nature of the world, that enables you to let your mind spread out,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and empathize, and enhance the basic human ability of empathizing,"},{"time":413000,"text":"and realizing that you are the other being,"},{"time":416000,"text":"somehow by that opening, you can see the deeper nature of life. And you can,"},{"time":422000,"text":"you get away from this terrible iron circle of I, me, me, mine,"},{"time":430000,"text":"like the Beatles used to sing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"You know, we really learned everything in the '60s."},{"time":434000,"text":"Too bad nobody ever woke up to it,"},{"time":438000,"text":"and they've been trying to suppress it since then."},{"time":440000,"text":"I, me, me, mine. It's like a perfect song, that song. A perfect teaching."},{"time":445000,"text":"But when we're relieved from that,"},{"time":448000,"text":"we somehow then become interested in all the other beings."},{"time":450000,"text":"And we feel ourselves differently. It's totally strange."},{"time":454000,"text":"It's totally strange."},{"time":456000,"text":"The Dalai Lama always likes to say --"},{"time":459000,"text":"he says that when you give birth in your mind to the idea of compassion,"},{"time":464000,"text":"it's because you realize that you yourself and your pains and pleasures"},{"time":468000,"text":"are finally too small a theater for your intelligence."},{"time":472000,"text":"It's really too boring whether you feel like this or like that, or what, you know --"},{"time":477000,"text":"and the more you focus on how you feel, by the way, the worse it gets."},{"time":483000,"text":"Like, even when you're having a good time,"},{"time":485000,"text":"when is the good time over?"},{"time":487000,"text":"The good time is over when you think, how good is it?"},{"time":491000,"text":"And then it's never good enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"I love that Leilei said that the way of helping those who are suffering badly"},{"time":499000,"text":"on the physical plane or on other planes is having a good time,"},{"time":504000,"text":"doing it by having a good time."},{"time":506000,"text":"I think the Dalai Lama should have heard that. I wish he'd been there to hear that."},{"time":509000,"text":"He once told me -- he looked kind of sad;"},{"time":511000,"text":"he worries very much about the haves and have-nots."},{"time":513000,"text":"He looked a little sad, because he said, well, a hundred years ago,"},{"time":517000,"text":"they went and took everything away from the haves."},{"time":520000,"text":"You know, the big communist revolutions, Russia and China and so forth."},{"time":523000,"text":"They took it all away by violence,"},{"time":525000,"text":"saying they were going to give it to everyone, and then they were even worse."},{"time":529000,"text":"They didn't help at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"So what could possibly change this terrible gap that has opened up in the world today?"},{"time":537000,"text":"And so then he looks at me."},{"time":539000,"text":"So I said, \"Well, you know, you're all in this yourself. You teach: it's generosity,\""},{"time":544000,"text":"was all I could think of. What is virtue?"},{"time":547000,"text":"But of course, what you said, I think the key to saving the world, the key to compassion"},{"time":553000,"text":"is that it is more fun."},{"time":557000,"text":"It should be done by fun. Generosity is more fun. That's the key."},{"time":562000,"text":"Everybody has the wrong idea. They think Buddha was so boring,"},{"time":566000,"text":"and they're so surprised when they meet Dalai Lama and he's fairly jolly."},{"time":570000,"text":"Even though his people are being genocided --"},{"time":572000,"text":"and believe me, he feels every blow on every old nun's head,"},{"time":577000,"text":"in every Chinese prison. He feels it."},{"time":580000,"text":"He feels the way they are harvesting yaks nowadays."},{"time":583000,"text":"I won't even say what they do. But he feels it."},{"time":587000,"text":"And yet he's very jolly. He's extremely jolly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"Because when you open up like that,"},{"time":594000,"text":"then you can't just -- what good does it do to add being miserable with others' misery?"},{"time":600000,"text":"You have to find some vision where you see how hopeful it is,"},{"time":603000,"text":"how it can be changed."},{"time":605000,"text":"Look at that beautiful thing Chiho showed us. She scared us with the lava man."},{"time":609000,"text":"She scared us with the lava man is coming,"},{"time":612000,"text":"then the tsunami is coming,"},{"time":614000,"text":"but then finally there were flowers and trees, and it was very beautiful."},{"time":620000,"text":"It's really lovely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"So, compassion means to feel the feelings of others,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and the human being actually is compassion."},{"time":631000,"text":"The human being is almost out of time."},{"time":635000,"text":"The human being is compassion because what is our brain for?"},{"time":639000,"text":"Now, Jim's brain is memorizing the almanac."},{"time":645000,"text":"But he could memorize all the needs of all the beings that he is, he will, he did."},{"time":650000,"text":"He could memorize all kinds of fantastic things to help many beings."},{"time":655000,"text":"And he would have tremendous fun doing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658000,"text":"So the first person who gets happy,"},{"time":660000,"text":"when you stop focusing on the self-centered situation of, how happy am I,"},{"time":665000,"text":"where you're always dissatisfied --"},{"time":667000,"text":"as Mick Jagger told us. You never get any satisfaction that way."},{"time":672000,"text":"So then you decide, \"Well, I'm sick of myself."},{"time":674000,"text":"I'm going to think of how other people can be happy."},{"time":677000,"text":"I'm going to get up in the morning and think,"},{"time":678000,"text":"what can I do for even one other person, even a dog, my dog, my cat,"},{"time":682000,"text":"my pet, my butterfly?\""},{"time":685000,"text":"And the first person who gets happy when you do that,"},{"time":687000,"text":"you don't do anything for anybody else, but you get happier, you yourself,"},{"time":692000,"text":"because your whole perception broadens"},{"time":695000,"text":"and you suddenly see the whole world and all of the people in it."},{"time":699000,"text":"And you realize that this -- being with these people --"},{"time":701000,"text":"is the flower garden that Chiho showed us."},{"time":703000,"text":"It is Nirvana."},{"time":705000,"text":"And my time is up. And I know the TED commandments."},{"time":707000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}